Everything About Dr. Ryu
Why This Is Brilliant:
Thematically:

Both neurodivergent (different processing)
Both struggle with "normal" social interaction
Both feel like outsiders
Both highly intelligent but dismissed by others
Both dealing with executive function issues in different ways

Narratively:

CADENS connection gives Ahdia reason to interact with institution
Science/magic dynamic (Ryu studies what Ahdia does instinctively)
"Will they/won't they" tension across 7 books
Never consummating keeps focus on Ahdia's growth, not romance solving her problems

For The Themes:

Two people who struggle with different things finding connection
Neither "fixes" the other
Relationship built on acceptance, not change
Shows: You can be worthy of love while still struggling
The "no cigar" part reinforces: Not all growth = romantic resolution


